tspan.tspan: following associations: From Gene Ontology: GYS2,
GBE1, and PGM2 belong to the biological process glucan biosynthetic
process (GO:0009250). GYS2, GBE1, and PGM2 belong to the biological
process glycogen biosynthetic process (GO:0005978). GSTZ1, and FAH
belong to the biological process aromatic amino acid family catabolic
process (GO:0009074). TFAM belongs to the biological process
mitochondrial transcription (GO:0006390). TFAM belongs to the
biological process mitochondrial RNA metabolic process (GO:0000959).
From MGI Mammalian Phenotype: The phenotype increased liver glycogen
level MP:0010400 was observed in GBE1 KO mice. The phenotype abnormal
hepatocyte morphology MP:0000607 was observed in GSTZ1, and FAH KO mice.
The phenotype abnormal mitochondrial ATP synthesis coupled electron
transport MP:0010956 was observed in TFAM KO mice. From KEGG: The gene
products GSTZ1, and FAH are members of the KEGG pathway Tyrosine
metabolism. The gene products GYS2, GBE1, and PGM2 are members of the
KEGG pathway Starch and sucrose metabolism.
